io.debezium.relational.ddl

Class DataTypeGrammarParser

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.debezium.relational.ddl.DataTypeGrammarParser

  • @Immutable
public class DataTypeGrammarParser
extends java.lang.Object
    A parser for data type grammars that produces one DataTypeGrammarParser.DataTypePattern for a grammar, where the DataTypeGrammarParser.DataTypePattern can be used when parsing content containing data types adhering to the grammar(s).

    The grammar using the following rules:

    • Uppercase keyword or word tokens are considered literals that much be matched case-insensitively but completely.
    • Lowercase keyword or word tokens are considered logical names of a variable and will match and single token.
    • Optional tokens are delimited by '[' and ']' characters.
    • The type length, L (or mantissa, M) is specified with '(L)' or '(M)', or if coupled with a scale, S, with '(L,S)' or '(M,D)'. In these cases, the length will match any positive long, and scale will match any integer value. When the length or scale are represented with integers, they will match only those values.
    • The type may have a length of ..., in which case the parser will allow (but not capture) a list of values.
    • The literal '{n}' signals that the grammar can allow array dimensions at this point.

    For example, the following are valid data type grammars:

    • BIT
    • BIT(3) will match when the length is exactly 3 and will not match BIT(2).
    • DECIMAL(L[,S]) will match DECIMAL(5) and DECIMAL (10,3)
    • INTEGER{n} will match INTEGER[3], which is an array of integers.
    • ENUM(...) will match ENUM(a,b,c,d) and ENUM(a).
    See Also:
    DataTypeParser
